{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Okay, so"},{"time":2000,"text":"90 percent of my photographic process"},{"time":5000,"text":"is, in fact, not photographic."},{"time":7000,"text":"It involves a campaign of letter writing,"},{"time":10000,"text":"research and phone calls"},{"time":12000,"text":"to access my subjects,"},{"time":14000,"text":"which can range from Hamas leaders in Gaza"},{"time":17000,"text":"to a hibernating black bear in its cave"},{"time":20000,"text":"in West Virginia."},{"time":23000,"text":"And oddly, the most notable"},{"time":26000,"text":"letter of rejection I ever received"},{"time":28000,"text":"came from Walt Disney World,"},{"time":30000,"text":"a seemingly innocuous site."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32000,"text":"And it read -- I'm just going to read a key sentence:"},{"time":35000,"text":"\"Especially during these violent times,"},{"time":38000,"text":"I personally believe"},{"time":40000,"text":"that the magical spell cast upon guests who visit our theme parks"},{"time":44000,"text":"is particularly important to protect"},{"time":47000,"text":"and helps to provide them with an important fantasy"},{"time":49000,"text":"they can escape to.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"Photography threatens fantasy."},{"time":54000,"text":"They didn't want to let my camera in"},{"time":56000,"text":"because it confronts constructed realities, myths and beliefs,"},{"time":60000,"text":"and provides what appears to be"},{"time":63000,"text":"evidence of a truth."},{"time":65000,"text":"But there are multiple truths attached to every image,"},{"time":68000,"text":"depending on the creator's intention, the viewer"},{"time":71000,"text":"and the context in which it is presented."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75000,"text":"Over a five year period following September 11th,"},{"time":78000,"text":"when the American media and government were seeking"},{"time":80000,"text":"hidden and unknown sites"},{"time":82000,"text":"beyond its borders,"},{"time":84000,"text":"most notably weapons of mass destruction,"},{"time":87000,"text":"I chose to look inward at that which was integral"},{"time":90000,"text":"to America's foundation,"},{"time":92000,"text":"mythology and daily functioning."},{"time":94000,"text":"I wanted to confront the boundaries of the citizen,"},{"time":97000,"text":"self-imposed and real,"},{"time":99000,"text":"and confront the divide between privileged"},{"time":102000,"text":"and public access to knowledge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106000,"text":"It was a critical moment in American history"},{"time":109000,"text":"and global history"},{"time":111000,"text":"where one felt they didn't have access to accurate information."},{"time":114000,"text":"And I wanted to see the center with my own eyes,"},{"time":118000,"text":"but what I came away with is a photograph."},{"time":121000,"text":"And it's just another place from which to observe,"},{"time":123000,"text":"and the understanding that"},{"time":125000,"text":"there are no absolute, all-knowing insiders."},{"time":128000,"text":"And the outsider can never really reach the core."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133000,"text":"I'm going to run through some of the photographs in this series."},{"time":137000,"text":"It's titled, \"An American Index"},{"time":139000,"text":"of the Hidden and Unfamiliar,\""},{"time":141000,"text":"and it's comprised of nearly 70 images."},{"time":144000,"text":"In this context I'll just show you a few."},{"time":146000,"text":"This is a nuclear waste storage and encapsulation facility"},{"time":151000,"text":"at Hanford site in Washington State,"},{"time":153000,"text":"where there are over 1,900"},{"time":155000,"text":"stainless steel capsules containing nuclear waste"},{"time":157000,"text":"submerged in water."},{"time":159000,"text":"A human standing in front of an unprotected capsule would die instantly."},{"time":163000,"text":"And I found one section amongst all of these"},{"time":166000,"text":"that actually resembled the outline"},{"time":168000,"text":"of the United States of America,"},{"time":170000,"text":"which you can see here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172000,"text":"And a big part of the work that is"},{"time":174000,"text":"sort of absent in this context is text."},{"time":178000,"text":"So I create these two poles."},{"time":180000,"text":"Every image is accompanied with a very detailed factual text."},{"time":184000,"text":"And what I'm most interested in"},{"time":186000,"text":"is the invisible space between a text"},{"time":189000,"text":"and its accompanying image,"},{"time":191000,"text":"and how the image is transformed by the text"},{"time":194000,"text":"and the text by the image."},{"time":196000,"text":"So, at best, the image is meant to float away"},{"time":198000,"text":"into abstraction and multiple truths and fantasy."},{"time":202000,"text":"And then the text functions as this cruel anchor"},{"time":205000,"text":"that kind of nails it to the ground."},{"time":207000,"text":"But in this context I'm just going to read"},{"time":210000,"text":"an abridged version of those texts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212000,"text":"This is a cryopreservation unit,"},{"time":215000,"text":"and it holds the bodies of the wife and mother"},{"time":217000,"text":"of cryonics pioneer Robert Ettinger,"},{"time":219000,"text":"who hoped to be awoken one day to extended life"},{"time":222000,"text":"in good health, with advancements in science and technology,"},{"time":226000,"text":"all for the cost of 35 thousand dollars, for forever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231000,"text":"This is a 21-year-old Palestinian woman"},{"time":234000,"text":"undergoing hymenoplasty."},{"time":236000,"text":"Hymenoplasty is a surgical procedure which restores the virginal state,"},{"time":241000,"text":"allowing her to adhere to certain cultural expectations"},{"time":244000,"text":"regarding virginity and marriage."},{"time":246000,"text":"So it essentially reconstructs a ruptured hymen,"},{"time":249000,"text":"allowing her to bleed upon having sexual intercourse,"},{"time":253000,"text":"to simulate the loss of virginity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256000,"text":"This is a jury simulation deliberation room,"},{"time":259000,"text":"and you can see beyond that two-way mirror"},{"time":261000,"text":"jury advisers standing in a room behind the mirror."},{"time":265000,"text":"And they observe deliberations"},{"time":267000,"text":"after mock trial proceedings"},{"time":269000,"text":"so that they can better advise their clients how to adjust their trial strategy"},{"time":273000,"text":"to have the outcome that they're hoping for."},{"time":276000,"text":"This process costs 60,000 dollars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281000,"text":"This is a U.S. Customs and Border Protection room,"},{"time":285000,"text":"a contraband room, at John F. Kennedy International Airport."},{"time":288000,"text":"On that table you can see 48 hours' worth"},{"time":291000,"text":"of seized goods from passengers entering in to the United States."},{"time":295000,"text":"There is a pig's head and African cane rats."},{"time":299000,"text":"And part of my photographic work"},{"time":301000,"text":"is I'm not just documenting what's there."},{"time":304000,"text":"I do take certain liberties and intervene."},{"time":307000,"text":"And in this I really wanted it to resemble"},{"time":309000,"text":"an early still-life painting,"},{"time":311000,"text":"so I spent some time with the smells and items."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316000,"text":"This is the exhibited art on the walls of the CIA"},{"time":319000,"text":"in Langley, Virginia, their original headquarters building."},{"time":322000,"text":"And the CIA has had a long history"},{"time":325000,"text":"with both covert and public cultural diplomacy efforts."},{"time":329000,"text":"And it's speculated that some of their interest in the arts"},{"time":331000,"text":"was designed to counter Soviet communism"},{"time":334000,"text":"and promote what it considered to be pro-American"},{"time":336000,"text":"thoughts and aesthetics."},{"time":338000,"text":"And one of the art forms that elicited the interest of the agency,"},{"time":342000,"text":"and had thus come under question, is abstract expressionism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348000,"text":"This is the Forensic Anthropology Research Facility,"},{"time":352000,"text":"and on a six acre plot"},{"time":354000,"text":"there are approximately 75 cadavers at any given time"},{"time":358000,"text":"that are being studied by forensic anthropologists"},{"time":361000,"text":"and researchers who are interested in monitoring"},{"time":364000,"text":"a rate of corpse decomposition."},{"time":367000,"text":"And in this particular photograph the body of a young boy"},{"time":370000,"text":"has been used to reenact a crime scene."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374000,"text":"This is the only federally funded site"},{"time":377000,"text":"where it is legal to cultivate cannabis"},{"time":380000,"text":"for scientific research in the United States."},{"time":383000,"text":"It's a research crop marijuana grow room."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385000,"text":"And part of the work that I hope for"},{"time":388000,"text":"is that there is a sort of disorienting entropy"},{"time":391000,"text":"where you can't find any discernible formula in how these things --"},{"time":395000,"text":"they sort of awkwardly jump from government to science"},{"time":398000,"text":"to religion to security --"},{"time":400000,"text":"and you can't completely understand"},{"time":403000,"text":"how information is being distributed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407000,"text":"These are transatlantic submarine communication cables"},{"time":410000,"text":"that travel across the floor of the Atlantic Ocean,"},{"time":413000,"text":"connecting North America to Europe."},{"time":415000,"text":"They carry over 60 million simultaneous voice conversations,"},{"time":419000,"text":"and in a lot of the government and technology sites"},{"time":422000,"text":"there was just this very apparent vulnerability."},{"time":425000,"text":"This one is almost humorous because it feels like I could"},{"time":427000,"text":"just snip all of that conversation in one easy cut."},{"time":430000,"text":"But stuff did feel like it could have been taken"},{"time":434000,"text":"30 or 40 years ago, like it was locked in the Cold War era"},{"time":438000,"text":"and hadn't necessarily progressed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441000,"text":"This is a Braille edition of Playboy magazine."},{"time":444000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":446000,"text":"And this is ... a division of the Library of Congress"},{"time":448000,"text":"produces a free national library service"},{"time":452000,"text":"for the blind and visually impaired,"},{"time":454000,"text":"and the publications they choose to publish"},{"time":456000,"text":"are based on reader popularity."},{"time":459000,"text":"And Playboy is always in the top few."},{"time":461000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":463000,"text":"But you'd be surprised, they don't do the photographs. It's just the text."},{"time":467000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":468000,"text":"This is an avian quarantine facility"},{"time":470000,"text":"where all imported birds coming into America"},{"time":472000,"text":"are required to undergo a 30-day quarantine,"},{"time":475000,"text":"where they are tested for diseases"},{"time":477000,"text":"including Exotic Newcastle Disease"},{"time":479000,"text":"and Avian Influenza."},{"time":483000,"text":"This film shows"},{"time":487000,"text":"the testing of a new explosive fill on a warhead."},{"time":491000,"text":"And the Air Armament Center"},{"time":493000,"text":"at Eglin Air Force Base in Florida"},{"time":495000,"text":"is responsible for the deployment and testing"},{"time":497000,"text":"of all air-delivered weaponry"},{"time":500000,"text":"coming from the United States."},{"time":504000,"text":"And the film was shot on 72 millimeter, government-issue film."},{"time":508000,"text":"And that red dot is a marking on the government-issue film."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512000,"text":"All living white tigers in North America"},{"time":515000,"text":"are the result of selective inbreeding --"},{"time":517000,"text":"that would be mother to son,"},{"time":519000,"text":"father to daughter, sister to brother --"},{"time":521000,"text":"to allow for the genetic conditions"},{"time":524000,"text":"that create a salable white tiger."},{"time":526000,"text":"Meaning white fur, ice blue eyes, a pink nose."},{"time":530000,"text":"And the majority of these white tigers"},{"time":533000,"text":"are not born in a salable state"},{"time":535000,"text":"and are killed at birth."},{"time":537000,"text":"It's a very violent process that is little known."},{"time":540000,"text":"And the white tiger is obviously celebrated in several forms of entertainment."},{"time":545000,"text":"Kenny was born. He actually made it to adulthood."},{"time":548000,"text":"He has since passed away,"},{"time":550000,"text":"but was mentally retarded"},{"time":552000,"text":"and suffers from severe bone abnormalities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556000,"text":"This, on a lighter note, is at"},{"time":558000,"text":"George Lucas' personal archive."},{"time":561000,"text":"This is the Death Star."},{"time":563000,"text":"And it's shown here in its true orientation."},{"time":566000,"text":"In the context of \"Star Wars: Return of the Jedi,\""},{"time":568000,"text":"its mirror image is presented."},{"time":570000,"text":"They flip the negative."},{"time":572000,"text":"And you can see the photoetched brass detailing,"},{"time":575000,"text":"and the painted acrylic facade."},{"time":577000,"text":"In the context of the film,"},{"time":579000,"text":"this is a deep-space battle station of the Galactic Empire,"},{"time":582000,"text":"capable of annihilating planets and civilizations,"},{"time":586000,"text":"and in reality it measures about four feet by two feet."},{"time":589000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":593000,"text":"This is at Fort Campbell in Kentucky."},{"time":596000,"text":"It's a Military Operations on Urbanized Terrain site."},{"time":599000,"text":"Essentially they've simulated a city"},{"time":602000,"text":"for urban combat,"},{"time":604000,"text":"and this is one of the structures that exists in that city."},{"time":606000,"text":"It's called the World Church of God."},{"time":609000,"text":"It's supposed to be a generic site of worship."},{"time":612000,"text":"And after I took this photograph,"},{"time":615000,"text":"they constructed a wall around the World Church of God"},{"time":617000,"text":"to mimic the set-up of mosques in Afghanistan or Iraq."},{"time":622000,"text":"And I worked with Mehta Vihar"},{"time":624000,"text":"who creates virtual simulations for the army"},{"time":627000,"text":"for tactical practice."},{"time":629000,"text":"And we put that wall around the World Church of God,"},{"time":631000,"text":"and also used the characters and vehicles and explosions"},{"time":635000,"text":"that are offered in the video games for the army."},{"time":638000,"text":"And I put them into my photograph."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642000,"text":"This is live HIV virus"},{"time":644000,"text":"at Harvard Medical School, who is working with the U.S. Government"},{"time":646000,"text":"to develop sterilizing immunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650000,"text":"And Alhurra is a U.S. Government- sponsored"},{"time":653000,"text":"Arabic language television network"},{"time":656000,"text":"that distributes news and information to over 22 countries in the Arab world."},{"time":661000,"text":"It runs 24 hours a day, commercial free."},{"time":664000,"text":"However, it's illegal to broadcast Alhurra within the United States."},{"time":669000,"text":"And in 2004, they developed a channel called Alhurra Iraq,"},{"time":672000,"text":"which specifically deals with events occurring in Iraq"},{"time":675000,"text":"and is broadcast to Iraq."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678000,"text":"Now I'm going to move on to another project I did."},{"time":680000,"text":"It's titled \"The Innocents.\""},{"time":683000,"text":"And for the men in these photographs,"},{"time":685000,"text":"photography had been used to create a fantasy."},{"time":688000,"text":"Contradicting its function as evidence of a truth,"},{"time":691000,"text":"in these instances it furthered the fabrication of a lie."},{"time":695000,"text":"I traveled across the United States"},{"time":697000,"text":"photographing men and women who had been wrongfully convicted"},{"time":700000,"text":"of crimes they did not commit, violent crimes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704000,"text":"I investigate photography's ability to blur truth and fiction,"},{"time":708000,"text":"and its influence on memory,"},{"time":710000,"text":"which can lead to severe, even lethal consequences."},{"time":714000,"text":"For the men in these photographs,"},{"time":716000,"text":"the primary cause of their wrongful conviction"},{"time":718000,"text":"was mistaken identification."},{"time":721000,"text":"A victim or eyewitness identifies"},{"time":723000,"text":"a suspected perpetrator"},{"time":725000,"text":"through law enforcement's use of images."},{"time":728000,"text":"But through exposure to composite sketches,"},{"time":730000,"text":"Polaroids, mug shots and line-ups,"},{"time":733000,"text":"eyewitness testimony can change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":735000,"text":"I'll give you an example from a case."},{"time":738000,"text":"A woman was raped and presented with a series of photographs"},{"time":741000,"text":"from which to identify her attacker."},{"time":743000,"text":"She saw some similarities in one of the photographs,"},{"time":747000,"text":"but couldn't quite make a positive identification."},{"time":749000,"text":"Days later, she is presented with another photo array"},{"time":753000,"text":"of all new photographs,"},{"time":755000,"text":"except that one photograph that she had some draw to"},{"time":758000,"text":"from the earlier array is repeated in the second array."},{"time":761000,"text":"And a positive identification is made"},{"time":764000,"text":"because the photograph replaced the memory,"},{"time":766000,"text":"if there ever was an actual memory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770000,"text":"Photography offered the criminal justice system"},{"time":773000,"text":"a tool that transformed innocent citizens into criminals,"},{"time":776000,"text":"and the criminal justice system failed to recognize the limitations"},{"time":780000,"text":"of relying on photographic identifications."}]},{"cues":[{"time":784000,"text":"Frederick Daye, who is photographed at his alibi location,"},{"time":788000,"text":"where 13 witnesses placed him at the time of the crime."},{"time":791000,"text":"He was convicted by an all-white jury"},{"time":794000,"text":"of rape, kidnapping and vehicle theft."},{"time":796000,"text":"And he served 10 years of a life sentence."},{"time":800000,"text":"Now DNA exonerated Frederick"},{"time":802000,"text":"and it also implicated another man"},{"time":804000,"text":"who was serving time in prison."},{"time":806000,"text":"But the victim refused to press charges"},{"time":808000,"text":"because she claimed that law enforcement"},{"time":810000,"text":"had permanently altered her memory through the use of Frederick's photograph."}]},{"cues":[{"time":815000,"text":"Charles Fain was convicted of kidnapping, rape and murder"},{"time":819000,"text":"of a young girl walking to school."},{"time":821000,"text":"He served 18 years of a death sentence."},{"time":824000,"text":"I photographed him at the scene of the crime"},{"time":826000,"text":"at the Snake River in Idaho."},{"time":828000,"text":"And I photographed all of the wrongfully convicted"},{"time":832000,"text":"at sites that came to particular significance"},{"time":837000,"text":"in the history of their wrongful conviction."},{"time":839000,"text":"The scene of arrest, the scene of misidentification,"},{"time":841000,"text":"the alibi location."},{"time":843000,"text":"And here, the scene of the crime, it's this place"},{"time":845000,"text":"to which he's never been, but changed his life forever."},{"time":849000,"text":"So photographing there, I was hoping to highlight"},{"time":851000,"text":"the tenuous relationship between truth and fiction,"},{"time":854000,"text":"in both his life and in photography."}]},{"cues":[{"time":859000,"text":"Calvin Washington was convicted of capital murder."},{"time":862000,"text":"He served 13 years of a life sentence in Waco, Texas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867000,"text":"Larry Mayes, I photographed at the scene of arrest,"},{"time":870000,"text":"where he hid between two mattresses in Gary, Indiana,"},{"time":872000,"text":"in this very room to hide from the police."},{"time":876000,"text":"He ended up serving 18 and a half years"},{"time":878000,"text":"of an 80 year sentence for rape and robbery."},{"time":881000,"text":"The victim failed to identify Larry"},{"time":883000,"text":"in two live lineups"},{"time":885000,"text":"and then made a positive identification, days later,"},{"time":888000,"text":"from a photo array."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891000,"text":"Larry Youngblood served eight years of a 10 and half year sentence"},{"time":894000,"text":"in Arizona for the abduction and repeated sodomizing"},{"time":898000,"text":"of a 10 year old boy at a carnival."},{"time":901000,"text":"He is photographed at his alibi location."}]},{"cues":[{"time":905000,"text":"Ron Williamson. Ron was convicted of the rape and murder"},{"time":909000,"text":"of a barmaid at a club,"},{"time":911000,"text":"and served 11 years of a death sentence."},{"time":914000,"text":"I photographed Ron at a baseball field"},{"time":916000,"text":"because he had been drafted to the Oakland A's"},{"time":918000,"text":"to play professional baseball just before his conviction."},{"time":922000,"text":"And the state's key witness in Ron's case"},{"time":925000,"text":"was, in the end, the actual perpetrator."}]},{"cues":[{"time":930000,"text":"Ronald Jones served eight years of a death sentence"},{"time":934000,"text":"for rape and murder of a 28-year-old woman."},{"time":936000,"text":"I photographed him at the scene of arrest in Chicago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":941000,"text":"William Gregory was convicted of rape and burglary."},{"time":945000,"text":"He served seven years of a 70 year sentence in Kentucky."}]},{"cues":[{"time":950000,"text":"Timothy Durham, who I photographed at his alibi location"},{"time":953000,"text":"where 11 witnesses placed him at the time of the crime,"},{"time":956000,"text":"was convicted of 3.5 years"},{"time":958000,"text":"of a 3220 year sentence,"},{"time":963000,"text":"for several charges of rape and robbery."},{"time":965000,"text":"He had been misidentified by an 11-year-old victim."}]},{"cues":[{"time":970000,"text":"Troy Webb is photographed here at the scene of the crime in Virginia."},{"time":974000,"text":"He was convicted of rape, kidnapping and robbery,"},{"time":977000,"text":"and served seven years of a 47 year sentence."},{"time":981000,"text":"Troy's picture was in a photo array"},{"time":983000,"text":"that the victim tentatively had some draw toward,"},{"time":985000,"text":"but said he looked too old."},{"time":988000,"text":"The police went and found a photograph of Troy Webb"},{"time":991000,"text":"from four years earlier,"},{"time":993000,"text":"which they entered into a photo array days later,"},{"time":996000,"text":"and he was positively identified."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1000000,"text":"Now I'm going to leave you with a self portrait."},{"time":1004000,"text":"And it reiterates that distortion is a constant,"},{"time":1008000,"text":"and our eyes are easily deceived."},{"time":1021000,"text":"That's it. Thank you."},{"time":1023000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}